benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/invoiceItems/{invoiceItemId}/tags - Retrieve invoice item tags

covered: Valid Request: Multiple scenarios cover successful retrieval of tags with HTTP 200 and Tag schema validation across TC01–TC06, TC23.
Query Parameters: Broad coverage of accountId, includedDeleted, audit, and extra parameter handling across TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC06, TC11, TC13, TC14, TC15, TC16, TC17.

Error Handling: Comprehensive coverage of 400/401/404/503 responses for invalid inputs, missing parameters, and resource-not-found/back-end failures (TC07, TC08, TC09, TC10, TC11, TC12, TC13, TC14, TC18, TC19, TC20).
Security: SQL injection in invoiceItemId (TC19) and XSS payload in accountId (TC20).
Edge Cases: Tests for maximum/minimum UUID lengths (TC16-17) and extra query parameters (TC15).
System/Integration: Backend unavailability (TC18) and integration with downstream audit service (TC24-25).
State Variations: Empty and partially populated database scenarios (TC26-27) and deleted tag visibility scenarios (TC02, TC23).
Performance: Basic load and peak load tests (TC21-22) included as non-functional validation.
gaps: Pagination: No tests cover pagination handling for large datasets.
Authorization: Only 401 errors tested; no 403/insufficient-privilege scenarios.
Rate Limiting: No tests to verify rate limiting or throttling.
Caching Behavior: No tests validating caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control).
recommendations: Add pagination tests to validate correct page behavior and boundaries for large datasets.
Introduce 403 Forbidden tests to cover insufficient privileges with valid authentication.
Add rate-limiting/throttling tests to ensure stability under high load.
Add caching tests to verify ETag/Cache-Control headers and caching behavior.
